To compute the slope of the line of best fit, we first choose two points on the line. Our line appears to pass through one of the data points,(8.8, 139.6). Look for a second point on the line whose coordinates are easy to read, perhaps (6.5,100). The slope is
        m = \frac{139.6 - 100}{8.8 - 6.5}= 17.2\text{ miles per gallon}
    According to our data, the SUV gets about 17.2 miles to the gallon.
